message.content: cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC. The paper discusses an approach to question answering that involves alignment and information retrieval, which are common topics in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), respectively. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses unsupervised learning and proposes a simple baseline, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper compares its results to those of supervised recurrent neural networks, which are a popular approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and the paper discusses the performance of its approach on different datasets, which is relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC).
